sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Data Scientist
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Operator as KubeRay Operator
    participant CertMgr as cert-manager API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Gateway as data-science-gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant AuthProxy as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Dashboard as Ray Dashboard<br/>8265/TCP HTTP
    participant HeadPod as Ray Head Pod
    participant Workers as Ray Workers
    participant ServeSvc as Serve Service<br/>8000/TCP HTTP

    Note over User, ServeSvc: Flow 1: RayCluster Creation & Dashboard Access (OpenShift/RHOAI)
    User->>K8sAPI: 1. Create RayCluster CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: Watch event
    Operator->>K8sAPI: 2. Create Head Pod, Worker Pods,<br/>Services, RBAC<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    Operator->>CertMgr: 3. Create Issuer + Certificates<br/>for mTLS<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    CertMgr-->>Operator: Certificates issued

    Note over User, ServeSvc: Dashboard Access via Gateway
    User->>Gateway: 4. GET /ray/{ns}/{cluster}/<br/>Auth: Session cookie
    Gateway->>AuthProxy: 5. Forward request<br/>TLS (self-signed)<br/>Auth: SubjectAccessReview
    AuthProxy->>Dashboard: 6. Proxy to localhost<br/>HTTP (loopback)<br/>No auth
    Dashboard-->>AuthProxy: Dashboard response
    AuthProxy-->>Gateway: Response
    Gateway-->>User: Dashboard UI

    Note over User, ServeSvc: Flow 2: RayJob Submission (HTTP Mode)
    User->>K8sAPI: Create RayJob CR
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: Watch event
    Operator->>Dashboard: 1. POST /api/jobs/<br/>HTTP (cluster-internal)<br/>No auth
    Dashboard->>HeadPod: Schedule job
    HeadPod->>Workers: 2. Distribute tasks<br/>gRPC, mTLS (if enabled)
    Workers-->>HeadPod: Task results
    Operator->>Dashboard: 3. GET /api/jobs/{id}<br/>Poll status

    Note over User, ServeSvc: Flow 3: RayService Zero-Downtime Upgrade
    Operator->>Dashboard: 1. PUT Serve config<br/>on pending cluster<br/>8265/TCP HTTP
    Operator->>ServeSvc: 2. Health check<br/>8000/TCP HTTP
    ServeSvc-->>Operator: Health status
    Operator->>K8sAPI: 3. Switch Service selector<br/>active ↔ pending<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    User->>ServeSvc: 4. Client traffic<br/>8000/TCP HTTP<br/>Seamless cutover
